  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the different types of osmotic dysregulation in patients
      with Syndrome of Inappropriate ADH (SIADH) and, hence, to analyze the pathophysiology of
      SIADH.

      These types will be characterized by measurement of AVP and copeptin while performing an
      osmotic stimulation with infusion of hypertonic saline.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
